main event: On 25 June 1966, an unidentified object was observed in Houston, Texas for approximately 20-30 seconds.
interesting points: The object was stationary and estimated to be 600 feet above ground,The object was reported to be yellow-white in color with no visible exhaust or sound,The observer estimated the object's speed between 700 and 800 miles per hour,There were no other air traffic reports for that time,The case was concluded as insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: The observer's reliability was not specified, but they reported detailed observations.
